<h1>My beloved Silver Lady is a total loss due to a complete failure of the entire system.</h1>
<p><strong>&#34;<a href="https://ask.metafilter.com/375799/How-to-sell-a-vehicle-for-salvage-in-California?utm_source=perfectsentences&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=perfect-sentences-41" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">How to sell a vehicle for salvage in California?</a>&#34;, Metafilter</strong></p>
<p>Submitted by Bill, with the following commentary: &#34;I love this sentence because &#34;complete failure of the entire system&#34; is a claim that I kind of want to understand more deeply? But no: it opaquely lays claim to all possibilities. The failure is utter; the scope, unbounded.&#34;</p>

